        "Name": "Culverin",
        "Details": "Determined not to be left behind by the march of progress, the Armed Forces of the Federated Suns began work in the 3050s on a Superheavy BattleMech program. Despite a decade of fitful starts and stops, they eventually debuted a design in the 3060s, the Culverin. Named for an ancient Terran artillery weapon, the Culverin carries four of the AFFS's favored weapons, LB-10X Autocannons, into combat. To back up the barrage of autocannons the Culverin has a mere MML-7 and ER Small Laser, necessitating it remain close to supply lines lest its generous 8 tons of ammo run out. Most shockingly though, the Culverin is powered by a 405-rated XL engine, breaking the normal confines of what BattleMech engines can consist of.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
